		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">John Purugganan</span></strong> is serving a life sentence in a California prison. He is the author of the play <em>Let&rsquo;s Keep Dancing</em>, which won the first annual Arts in Correction Playwriting Contest in 1992, sponsored by <span class="smallcaps">UCLA</span>&rsquo;s extension program. He is currently seeking a production company for his screenplays <em>Blood Parable</em> and <em>Hush</em>. Correspondence can be sent to: John Purugganan <span class="smallcaps">E</span>-71364, <span class="smallcaps">CSC-LAC</span>/<span class="smallcaps">A</span>2-108, P.O. Box 4430, Lancaster, CA 93539.</p><a href="/contributors/john-purugganan" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
