			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1526">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>&ldquo;<a href="/article/187">You&rsquo;re In Prison</a>,&rdquo; by John Purugganan [October 2006], spoke to me. I know no one who is in prison, yet the humanity of his story supported the small voice in my head that says prisoners are not monsters but people with souls. It&rsquo;s easier to close our eyes, as our culture encourages, and pretend a convicted felon ceases to be human.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Marla Kiley<br>Denver, Colorado</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1527">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>As an inmate serving a life sentence, I can say that John Purugganan pinpoints both physically and emotionally what the experience is like. Yet, as I read his tale of guilt and remorse, I couldn&rsquo;t help but think: Is there no room for forgiveness? Is it wrong for me to forgive myself for the horrible, irreversible damage I have caused my victims? Is there no allowance for healing?</p>

<p>I do not see asking for forgiveness as a selfish insult. When I went through a victim-offender mediation program, I felt obligated not only to take full responsibility for my victims&rsquo; loss and pain, but also to ask for their forgiveness. I did this not so that I could minimize my crime and feel better about myself &mdash; their forgiveness cannot make me feel better about what I&rsquo;ve done &mdash; but to offer them an opportunity for healing. My own healing will have to come from forgiving myself.</p>

<p>And of course I do not deserve it! That&rsquo;s why it&rsquo;s called &ldquo;grace.&rdquo; If I deserved it, I wouldn&rsquo;t need forgiveness.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Stephen Stoeltje<br>Gatesville, Texas</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

				<div class="text-center">
			<button class="b b-1 xsmall js-b-readmore-correspondence" data-collapsible="#article-correspondences" data-label="Read More Letters">Read More Letters</button>
